    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a comparison and contrast paragraph on</span><span class=\"english\"> ‘Daydreamer vs Realist’ </span><span class=\"english\">within 10 sentences</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Daydreamer vs Realist</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Daydreamers and realists offer contrasting approaches to life, each with distinct advantages. Daydreamers thrive on imagination, exploring possibilities beyond the present and inspiring creativity and innovation. They often envision futures that others mig</span><span class=\"english\">ht overlook, driving progress in fields like art, science, and entrepreneurship. However, realists focus on practicality and the here-and-now, grounding decisions in what is achievable and tangible. While daydreamers may be criticized for being disconnecte</span><span class=\"english\">d from reality, realists are sometimes seen as overly cautious, limiting their potential to dream big. Realists excel at managing current resources, making them effective at problem-solving and planning. Daydreamers, on the other hand, can push boundaries </span><span class=\"english\">and challenge the status quo. Both mindsets are necessary, as daydreamers drive ambition while realists ensure goals are actionable. The ideal approach balances vision with pragmatism, allowing dreams to be realized through practical steps.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Daydreamer vs Realist</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">-------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> --------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">People often navigate life through different mindsets, with two prominent ones being those of daydreamers and realists.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) </span><span class=\"english\">Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Daydreamer vs Realist</span><span class=\"english\">) (Any 6) </span><span class=\"english\">---------------------------06 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Daydreamers thrive on imagination, exploring possibilities beyond the present.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Daydreamers drive progress in fields like art, science, and entrepreneurship.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Realists focus on practicality and what is achievable in the present moment.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Realists are effective at managing resources, problem-solving, and planning.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Daydreamers may be seen as disconnected from reality.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Realists can be viewed as overly cautious, limiting big dreams.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Daydreamers challenge the status quo and push boundaries.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Both perspectives are valuable—daydreamers bring vision, realists ensure feasibility.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(The ideal approach balances vision with pragmatism, allowing dreams to be realized through practical steps)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every</span><span class=\"english\">03</span><span class=\"english\">spelling/grammatical mistakes, </span><span class=\"english\">01 mark </span><span class=\"english\">has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para).</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
